---
const title = "Blog"

const txt = "Something"
const n = 1000

// define some colors here you want to repeat
// const colors = ["red", "white", "green"]
const colors = ["red", "orange", "yellow", "green", "cyan", "blue", "violet"]
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
        <title>{title}</title>
        <style define:vars={{colors}}>
            .repeated {
                text-shadow: 1px 1px black;
            }
        </style>
	</head>
	<body>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/about/">About</a>
        <a href="/blog/">Blog</a>

        <h1>{title}</h1>
		<p> Here's where I post some thoughts and stories </p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/posts/post-1"> Post 1 </a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts/post-2"> Post 2 </a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts/post-3"> Post 3 </a></li>
        </ul>

        <p>Nice. I can now change 2 HTML elements by changing a variable.</p>
        <p>But we can do more! ...Here's "{txt}" repeated is {n} times!</p>

        <ol>
            {Array(n).fill(0).map((_, i) => (
                <li
                    style={"color: " + colors[i % colors.length]}
                    class="repeated"
                >
                    {txt}
                </li>
            ))}
        </ol>

	</body>
</html>
